content: **in a comparative study of the ideas of two contemporary political thinkers, ????????? and ???? ?????, we find that ????????? portrays the role of religion in the political sphere of human life as extremely minimal, and at best, Prophet Muhammad (?) formed a government based on a civil contract. This is in contrast to Imam Khomeini, who has maximum expectations of the role of religion in politics and extends its scope beyond the Prophet (?) to the "just scholar."**
